{"title_page": "Ferit Odman", "text_new": "{{Infobox musical artist | <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject Musicians -->\n| name                = Ferit Odman\n| image               = Feritodman.png\n| image_size        = 250\n| landscape          = yes\n| caption             = Ferit Odman\n| background       = non_vocal_instrumentalist\n| birth_name       = \n| birth_date         =  {{birth date and age|1982|7|7}}\n| birth_place        = [[Bursa]], Turkey\n| origin                = [[Istanbul]], Turkey\n| genre               =  [[Jazz]]\n| occupation       = Musician, composer\n| instrument       = Drums\n| years_active    = 2000&ndash;present\n| label                = Equinox\n| associated_acts =\n| website            = {{URL|www.feritodman.com}}\n}}\n\n'''Ferit Odman''' is a jazz drummer based in [[Istanbul]], Turkey.\n\n== Education ==\nOdman started his music studies in Sweden as an AFS exchange student in 1999, then received a full scholarship to Istanbul Bilgi University in 2001, where he obtained his B.A. in Music. In 2004, he attended workshops at the School for Improvisation in New York City. He was given a Fulbright Scholarship<ref name=turkful>{{cite web|last=Turkish Fulbright Commission|title=Facebook post|url=https://m.facebook.com/FulbrightTurkiye/posts/127917730604591|publisher=Turkish Fulbright Commission|accessdate=23 September 2013}}</ref> to study at William Paterson University from 2006\u20132008.<ref>{{cite web|title=WP Magazine: Spotlight|url=http://www.wpunj.edu/news/wpmagazine/pdfs/wpmag_fall11_onlinesmall.pdf|publisher=William Patterson University|accessdate=23 September 2013}}</ref> \n\n== Performing career ==\nOdman began his professional career in 2000 at the age of eighteen. He spent two years playing in New York City while pursuing his graduate degree, performing and recording with [[Brian Lynch (musician)|Brian Lynch]], [[Vincent Herring]], [[Peter Washington]], [[Benny Golson]], [[Jacky Terrasson]], [[Mike Moreno]], [[Sean Jones (trumpeter)|Sean Jones]], [[Ernie Watts]], [[Stefano di Battista]], Bertha Hope, [[Jim Rotondi]], [[Alan Broadbent]], [[Alex Sipiagin]], and [[David Berkman]]. Odman also played with a number of vocalists, including [[Sheila Jordan]], [[Kevin Mahogany]], [[Allan Harris]], [[Mark Murphy (singer)|Mark Murphy]], Deborah Davis, Ive Mendes, and [[Hilary Kole]]. He has played at many New York City clubs and festivals.\n\nSince returning to Istanbul, Odman has been a mainstay on the Turkish jazz scene, performing and recording with Kerem G\u00f6rsev and TRT (Turkish Radio Television) Big Band, among others. He was invited to a number of international festivals as a bandleader, including the [[North Sea Jazz Festival]], the [[Istanbul Jazz Festival]], the Prishtina Jazz Festival in Kosovo; the International Ankara Jazz Festival, and the Rabobank Amersfoort Jazz Festival in the Netherlands.\n\nOdman was featured in the May 2011 issue of ''Jazz Inside'' magazine.<ref name=Inside>{{cite web|title=Jazz Inside Magazine: May 2011|url=http://jazzinsidemagazine.com/publications/guide/may-2011-1|publisher=Jazz Inside|accessdate=23 September 2013}}</ref>\n\n== Recording career ==\nIn 2010, he released ''Nommo'',<ref name=allmusicnommo>{{cite web|title=All Music Guide: Nommo|url=http://www.allmusic.com/album/nommo-mw0002097183|publisher=AllMusic.com|accessdate=23 September 2013}}</ref> featuring trumpeter [[Brian Lynch (musician)|Brian Lynch]], saxophonist [[Vincent Herring]], pianist [[Burak Bedikyan]] and bassist [[Peter Washington]]. In 2011, he released ''Autumn In New York'', featuring trumpeter [[Terell Stafford]], saxophonist [[Vincent Herring]], pianist Anthony Wonsey and bassist [[Peter Washington]].<ref name=aajautumn>{{cite web|last=Carey|first=William|title=All About Jazz review: Autumn In New York|url=http://www.allaboutjazz.com/php/article.php?id=41160#.UkByp4YhA-Q|publisher=All About Jazz|accessdate=23 September 2013}}</ref>\nIn 2016, he released an all analog (AAA) Vinyl ''Dameronia With Strings'', which is a tribute to [[Tadd Dameron]] with six strings and featuring trumpeter [[Terell Stafford]], pianist [[Danny Grissett]] and bassist [[Peter Washington]].<ref name=allmusicdameronia>{{cite web|title=All Music Guide: Dameronia With Strings|url=http://www.allmusic.com/album/dameronia-with-strings-mw0002913606|publisher=AllMusic.com|accessdate=9 March 2016}}</ref> ''[[Down Beat|Down beat]]'' magazine gave four stars to ''Dameronia with Strings'',<ref name=Downbeat2>{{cite web|last=Potter|first=Jeff|title=Dameronia with Strings|url=http://www.downbeat.com/digitaledition/2016/DB1605/58-59.html|publisher=Downbeat Magazine|accessdate=6 April 2016}}</ref> four stars to ''Autumn in New York'',<ref name=Downbeat>{{cite web|title=Downbeat Magazine (via Gretsch drums)|url=http://www.gretschdrums.com/?fa=artistdetail&id=1185|accessdate=23 September 2013}}</ref><ref name=dbautumn>{{cite web|last=Micaleff|first=Ken|title=Autumn In New York|url=http://twitpic.com/95zjvb|publisher=Downbeat Magazine|accessdate=23 September 2013}}</ref> and three and a half stars to ''Nommo''.<ref name=dbnommo>{{cite web|last=Brady|first=Shaun|title=Leading From Behind The Kit|url=http://twitpic.com/7aem8w|publisher=Downbeat Magazine|accessdate=23 September 2013}}</ref>\n\n== Awards and honors==\n* 2012 TCF (Turkish Cultural Foundation) Cultural Exchange Fellowship<ref name=tcf>{{cite web|title=Experiences and Observations of Fellows|url=http://www.turkishculturalfoundation.org/files/2012FellowsQuotes.pdf|publisher=Turkish Cultural Foundation|accessdate=23 September 2013}}</ref>  \n* 2014 Rotary Professional Excellence Award (District 2440)\n\n== Discography ==\n=== As leader ===\n* ''Nommo'' (Equinox, 2010)\n* ''Autumn in New York''  (Equinox, 2011)<ref>{{cite web|title=Downbeat Magazine (via Gretsch Drums)|url=http://www.gretschdrums.com/?fa=artistdetail&id=1185|publisher=Gretsch Drums|accessdate=23 September 2013}}</ref> \n* ''Dameronia with Strings'' (Equinox, 2015)\n* ''The Vinyl Collection'' (Equinox, 2017)<ref>{{cite web|title=Discogs |url=https://www.discogs.com/Ferit-Odman-The-Vinyl-Collection-Box-Set/release/10084764|publisher=Discogs|accessdate=15 April 2017}}</ref>\n\n=== As a sideman ===\n* [[Kenan Do\u011fulu]], ''\u0130htimaller'' (2016 Do\u011fulu Productions)<ref>\n{{cite web|title=Discogs|url=http://www.discogs.com/artist/1991533-Ferit-Odman?filter_anv=0&type=Credits|publisher=Discogs.com |accessdate=10 June 2016}}</ref>\n* [[Fatih Erko\u00e7]], ''True Love'' (2016 Esen Elektronik)\n* Sinan Isik, ''Patience'' (2016)\n* Kerem G\u00f6rsev Trio & [[Ernie Watts]], ''Four Days'' (2015 Rec Jazz)\n* Bulut G\u00fclen, ''Su'' (2015 A.K. M\u00fczik)\n* [[Ozan Musluoglu]], ''My Best Friends Are Vocalists'' (2015 Sony Music Entertainment Turkey)\n* Kerem G\u00f6rsev Trio & [[Ernie Watts]], ''Emirgan'' (2014 Rec Jazz)\n* K\u0119stutis Vaiginis, ''Lights Of Darkness'' (2014 KV)\n* Kerem G\u00f6rsev & [[City of Prague Philharmonic Orchestra]], ''To Bill Evans'' (2013 Rec Jazz)\n* Asena Akan, ''Istanbul'un Izleri'' (2013 Kalan)\n* Ozan Musluoglu, ''My Best Friends Are Pianists'' (2012 Equinox Music & Entertainment)\n* \u00d6nder Focan, ''Songbook'' (2012 Equinox Music & Entertainment)\n* Kerem G\u00f6rsev & London [[Philharmonia Orchestra]], ''Therapy'' (2011 Rec Jazz)\n* [[Sezen Aksu]], ''\u00d6pt\u00fcm'' (2011 SN Music)\n* Uraz K\u0131vaner, ''Pieces'' (2011 Rec Jazz)\n* Ayhan Sicimo\u011flu, ''En Estambul'' (2011 IMM)\n* Joy Voeth, ''I Wish You Love'' (2010 JoyVoeth)\n* Jehan Barbur, ''Hayat'' (2010 ADA M\u00fczik)\n* Danielle Eva, ''Road and Moon'' (2010 Devour Music)\n* \u00dclkem \u00d6zsezen, ''Ghost\u2019s Note'' (2010 San Grafik)\n* Jef Giansily, ''Sketches'' (2009 Circle) \n* Kerem G\u00f6rsev, ''Diversion'' (2009 Rec Jazz) \n* Ozan Musluoglu, ''Coincidence'' (2009 Rec Jazz) \n* \u00d6nder Focan Group, ''Swing A La Turc'' (2007 Kalan Music) \n* SPIN, ''Ilk'' (2006 Aura Records) \n* Donovan Mixon, ''The Dance of Life'' (2004 DMC-Jazz)\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.feritodman.com Official site]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Odman, Ferit}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1982 births]]\n[[Category:William Paterson University alumni]]\n[[Category:Fulbright Scholars]]\n[[Category:Turkish jazz drummers]]\n[[Category:21st-century drummers]]\n[[Category:Turkish Jazz Musicians]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox musical artist | <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject Musicians -->\n| name                = Ferit Odman\n| image               = Feritodman.png\n| image_size        = 250\n| landscape          = yes\n| caption             = Ferit Odman\n| background       = non_vocal_instrumentalist\n| birth_name       = \n| birth_date         =  {{birth date and age|1982|7|7}}\n| birth_place        = [[Bursa]], Turkey\n| origin                = [[Istanbul]], Turkey\n| genre               =  [[Jazz]]\n| occupation       = Musician, composer\n| instrument       = Drums\n| years_active    = 2000&ndash;present\n| label                = Equinox\n| associated_acts =\n| website            = {{URL|www.feritodman.com}}\n}}\n\n'''Ferit Odman''' is a jazz drummer based in [[Istanbul]], Turkey.\n\n== Education ==\nOdman started his music studies in Sweden as an AFS exchange student in 1999, then received a full scholarship to Istanbul Bilgi University in 2001, where he obtained his B.A. in Music. In 2004, he attended workshops at the School for Improvisation in New York City. He was given a Fulbright Scholarship<ref name=turkful>{{cite web|last=Turkish Fulbright Commission|title=Facebook post|url=https://m.facebook.com/FulbrightTurkiye/posts/127917730604591|publisher=Turkish Fulbright Commission|accessdate=23 September 2013}}</ref> to study at William Paterson University from 2006\u20132008.<ref>{{cite web|title=WP Magazine: Spotlight|url=http://www.wpunj.edu/news/wpmagazine/pdfs/wpmag_fall11_onlinesmall.pdf|publisher=William Patterson University|accessdate=23 September 2013}}</ref> \n\n== Performing career ==\nOdman began his professional career in 2000 at the age of eighteen. He spent two years playing in New York City while pursuing his graduate degree, performing and recording with [[Brian Lynch (musician)|Brian Lynch]], [[Vincent Herring]], [[Peter Washington]], [[Benny Golson]], [[Jacky Terrasson]], [[Mike Moreno]], [[Sean Jones (trumpeter)|Sean Jones]], [[Ernie Watts]], [[Stefano di Battista]], Bertha Hope, [[Jim Rotondi]], [[Alan Broadbent]], [[Alex Sipiagin]], and [[David Berkman]]. Odman also played with a number of vocalists, including [[Sheila Jordan]], [[Kevin Mahogany]], [[Allan Harris]], [[Mark Murphy (singer)|Mark Murphy]], Deborah Davis, Ive Mendes, and [[Hilary Kole]]. He has played at many New York City clubs and festivals.\n\nSince returning to Istanbul, Odman has been a mainstay on the Turkish jazz scene, performing and recording with Kerem G\u00f6rsev and TRT (Turkish Radio Television) Big Band, among others. He was invited to a number of international festivals as a bandleader, including the [[North Sea Jazz Festival]], the [[Istanbul Jazz Festival]], the Prishtina Jazz Festival in Kosovo; the International Ankara Jazz Festival, and the Rabobank Amersfoort Jazz Festival in the Netherlands.\n\nOdman was featured in the May 2011 issue of ''Jazz Inside'' magazine.<ref name=Inside>{{cite web|title=Jazz Inside Magazine: May 2011|url=http://jazzinsidemagazine.com/publications/guide/may-2011-1|publisher=Jazz Inside|accessdate=23 September 2013}}</ref>\n\n== Recording career ==\nIn 2010, he released ''Nommo'',<ref name=allmusicnommo>{{cite web|title=All Music Guide: Nommo|url=http://www.allmusic.com/album/nommo-mw0002097183|publisher=AllMusic.com|accessdate=23 September 2013}}</ref> featuring trumpeter [[Brian Lynch (musician)|Brian Lynch]], saxophonist [[Vincent Herring]], pianist [[Burak Bedikyan]] and bassist [[Peter Washington]]. In 2011, he released ''Autumn In New York'', featuring trumpeter [[Terell Stafford]], saxophonist [[Vincent Herring]], pianist Anthony Wonsey and bassist [[Peter Washington]].<ref name=aajautumn>{{cite web|last=Carey|first=William|title=All About Jazz review: Autumn In New York|url=http://www.allaboutjazz.com/php/article.php?id=41160#.UkByp4YhA-Q|publisher=All About Jazz|accessdate=23 September 2013}}</ref>\nIn 2016, he released an all analog (AAA) Vinyl ''Dameronia With Strings'', which is a tribute to [[Tadd Dameron]] with six strings and featuring trumpeter [[Terell Stafford]], pianist [[Danny Grissett]] and bassist [[Peter Washington]].<ref name=allmusicdameronia>{{cite web|title=All Music Guide: Dameronia With Strings|url=http://www.allmusic.com/album/dameronia-with-strings-mw0002913606|publisher=AllMusic.com|accessdate=9 March 2016}}</ref> ''[[Down Beat|Down beat]]'' magazine gave four stars to ''Dameronia with Strings'',<ref name=Downbeat2>{{cite web|last=Potter|first=Jeff|title=Dameronia with Strings|url=http://www.downbeat.com/digitaledition/2016/DB1605/58-59.html|publisher=Downbeat Magazine|accessdate=6 April 2016}}</ref> four stars to ''Autumn in New York'',<ref name=Downbeat>{{cite web|title=Downbeat Magazine (via Gretsch drums)|url=http://www.gretschdrums.com/?fa=artistdetail&id=1185|accessdate=23 September 2013}}</ref><ref name=dbautumn>{{cite web|last=Micaleff|first=Ken|title=Autumn In New York|url=http://twitpic.com/95zjvb|publisher=Downbeat Magazine|accessdate=23 September 2013}}</ref> and three and a half stars to ''Nommo''.<ref name=dbnommo>{{cite web|last=Brady|first=Shaun|title=Leading From Behind The Kit|url=http://twitpic.com/7aem8w|publisher=Downbeat Magazine|accessdate=23 September 2013}}</ref>\n\n== Awards and honors==\n* 2012 TCF (Turkish Cultural Foundation) Cultural Exchange Fellowship<ref name=tcf>{{cite web|title=Experiences and Observations of Fellows|url=http://www.turkishculturalfoundation.org/files/2012FellowsQuotes.pdf|publisher=Turkish Cultural Foundation|accessdate=23 September 2013}}</ref>  \n* 2014 Rotary Professional Excellence Award (District 2440)\n\n== Discography ==\n=== As leader ===\n* ''Nommo'' (Equinox, 2010)\n* ''Autumn in New York''  (Equinox, 2011)<ref>{{cite web|title=Downbeat Magazine (via Gretsch Drums)|url=http://www.gretschdrums.com/?fa=artistdetail&id=1185|publisher=Gretsch Drums|accessdate=23 September 2013}}</ref> \n* ''Dameronia with Strings'' (Equinox, 2015)\n* ''The Vinyl Collection'' (Equinox, 2017)<ref>{{cite web|title=Discogs |url=https://www.discogs.com/Ferit-Odman-The-Vinyl-Collection-Box-Set/release/10084764|publisher=Discogs|accessdate=15 April 2017}}</ref>\n\n=== As a sideman ===\n* [[Kenan Do\u011fulu]], ''\u0130htimaller'' (2016 Do\u011fulu Productions)<ref>\n{{cite web|title=Discogs|url=http://www.discogs.com/artist/1991533-Ferit-Odman?filter_anv=0&type=Credits|publisher=Discogs.com |accessdate=10 June 2016}}</ref>\n* [[Fatih Erko\u00e7]], ''True Love'' (2016 Esen Elektronik)\n* Sinan Isik, ''Patience'' (2016)\n* Kerem G\u00f6rsev Trio & [[Ernie Watts]], ''Four Days'' (2015 Rec Jazz)\n* Bulut G\u00fclen, ''Su'' (2015 A.K. M\u00fczik)\n* [[Ozan Musluoglu]], ''My Best Friends Are Vocalists'' (2015 Sony Music Entertainment Turkey)\n* Kerem G\u00f6rsev Trio & [[Ernie Watts]], ''Emirgan'' (2014 Rec Jazz)\n* K\u0119stutis Vaiginis, ''Lights Of Darkness'' (2014 KV)\n* Kerem G\u00f6rsev & [[City of Prague Philharmonic Orchestra]], ''To Bill Evans'' (2013 Rec Jazz)\n* Asena Akan, ''Istanbul'un Izleri'' (2013 Kalan)\n* Ozan Musluoglu, ''My Best Friends Are Pianists'' (2012 Equinox Music & Entertainment)\n* \u00d6nder Focan, ''Songbook'' (2012 Equinox Music & Entertainment)\n* Kerem G\u00f6rsev & London [[Philharmonia Orchestra]], ''Therapy'' (2011 Rec Jazz)\n* [[Sezen Aksu]], ''\u00d6pt\u00fcm'' (2011 SN Music)\n* Uraz K\u0131vaner, ''Pieces'' (2011 Rec Jazz)\n* Ayhan Sicimo\u011flu, ''En Estambul'' (2011 IMM)\n* Joy Voeth, ''I Wish You Love'' (2010 JoyVoeth)\n* Jehan Barbur, ''Hayat'' (2010 ADA M\u00fczik)\n* Danielle Eva, ''Road and Moon''